In this article, President Trump signs an executive order to establish a regulatory reform task force that will research unnecessary, burdensome, and harmful regulations. The task force will make recommendations to repeal or simplify existing regulations. Trump emphasizes that excessive regulation is killing jobs and driving companies out of the country, and he aims to reduce the regulatory burden for businesses. He also mentions that he has already issued an order stating that for every new regulation, two old regulations must be eliminated. Trump believes that every regulation should pass a test of whether it makes life better or safer for American workers or consumers, and if it doesn't, it will be eliminated quickly. The president expresses his commitment to rolling back regulations to create more opportunities for businesses to prosper. He thanks the business leaders present at the signing and acknowledges their success in helping to shape policies that benefit businesses.